[1] Paraguay (Asuncion)
Date: 22 Jan 2007
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Yahoo Noticias, Telemando [trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://espanol.news.yahoo.com/s/ap/070121/salud/ams_gen_paraguay_dengue>

A 41-year-old woman is the 1st fatal case of dengue hemorrhagic fever
(DHF) this year [2007], confirmed by a Ministry of Health physician
on Sunday [21 Jan 2007].
Ivan Allende, Director of the Department of Transmissible Diseases,
informed the press that before she died, the woman indicated that
several weeks before she had been in cities in the department [state
or province equivalent. - Mod.TY] of Caagauzu, where the mosquito
_Aedes aegypti_ is abundant.
The Minister of Health, Oscar Martinez, indicated that in January of
this year [2007], 400 cases of dengue have been recorded, "but the
estimates are that if the population does not collaborate with [the
implementation] of preventive measures, the number of cases could
reach 400 000."
Allende indicated that in 2006, there were 1600 cases.
--
