[2] Philippines (Bayugan)
Date: 22 Jan 2007
From: A-Lan Banks <A-Lan.Banks@thomson.com>
Source: GMA news.tv-Quezon City, Metro Manila, Philippines [edited]
<http://www.gmanews.tv/story/27680/Dengue-outbreak-kills-4-in-Bayugan-Agusan-del-Sur>

At least 4 persons had died while 12 others, mostly minors, were
hospitalized in Bayugan town, Agusan del Sur [Province] in what
health authorities fear to be a dengue outbreak.
Sun-Star Cagayan de Oro reported Mon 19 Jan 2007 that at least 13
other persons are undergoing treatment.
Bayugan is a 1st class town in Agusan del Sur province with a
population of 93 623 people in 17 222 households.
Town mayor Magdalena Asis and municipal nurse Helen Saligan said most
of the victims are aged 1-4. They will submit on Mon 19 Jan 2007 an
official list and breakdown in age grouping.
Health authorities said they already conducted fumigation of areas
affected and conducted information and dissemination campaigns. Yet
Asis said 3 weeks of continuous rains have afflicted schoolchildren
at a local school in Barangay Poblacion with dengue fever. At least 2
had died from dengue, with 13 cases last month [December 2006], while
2 others, mostly one-year-olds, were killed this January 2007.
Saligan voiced fears the number may rise if no immediate remedies are
installed. Government officials have already asked for support from
the provincial government to contain the diseases affecting mostly
poor people in the area.
A "bandillo system" is in place among houses and puroks [puroks are a
political-geographic subdivision such as a city block] to inform
residents about the possible spread of the diseases in affected areas
by barangay [larger political-geographic subdivision that may contain
several puroks] and municipal officials.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
